Brittni Ann Waldow
i responded: it's not like the behavior is at all glamorized or made to appear "cool" and "acceptable." in fact, i think it, in a way, hauntingly mirrors (not to the same degree, obviously) the crimes they are investigating against women and children in the first place. here you have marty, this self-proclaimed believer in god and family man, who's fucking his stenographer behind his wife's back, and when that goes sour, he essentially breaks into the girls apartment and beats the shit out of the guy, gives money to some young whore at a brothel and years later cheats on his wife AGAIN with her, and then, smacks the shit out of his own daughter in a fit of rage. the macho-ness of it all is necessary for the plot line, in my opinion. i don't think this show is dangerous in the sense that it is normalizing rape culture OR violence against women. i think it paints a pretty harrowing picture of the life behind who society deems to be "the good guy" in showing how ugly a man can be regardless of his badge. i think it does absolutely no favors to male egotists, quite the opposite in fact. sure, this particular anthology series lacks a strong female character, but not everything in art, media, cinema, etc can always be fem oriented (trust me, i hate to say that), and having that super weak, flimsy "nothing burger" of a female lead, can in a way, make for comparison to strong, can-do women? we can look at her and go, "wow, what a pathetic, lifeless person. what a weak human being." and i think THAT in itself is almost just as good as having some power house of a woman character. not to mention, this series still has two episodes, so who knows what kind of twists and turns it could take. will marty be vindicated for all of his shitty behavior? or will he pay for it? what the fuck is rust's story and where is it all going? does the girl from the brothel or marty's husband play a strong role toward the end in wrapping up this case? who's to say. not to mention, i would be SHOCKED if there isn't a true detective series already in the works with that STRONG WONDER WOMAN character we want. Sit tight! But I dunno, this article is kind of one of those, "OH GIVE ME A FUCKIN BREAK" feminist rants. :X SORRY I SAID IT.
